# BootHarness ‚Äî Cursor AI Rules

Spring Boot 3.x SaaS backend starter kit. Backend API only ‚Äî no frontend included.

## Project structure

```
com.bootharness
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ auth/        JWT, OAuth2 (Google/GitHub), email+password, password reset
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ billing/     Stripe subscriptions, webhooks, Customer Portal
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ email/       Resend API, transactional email templates
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ user/        User entity, profile endpoints
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ api/         Global error handling (RFC 7807 ProblemDetail)
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ config/      Security, CORS, AppProperties, beans
```

## Architecture rules

- Feature-based packaging ‚Äî all classes for a feature live in one package
- Layered within each package: `Controller ‚Üí Service ‚Üí Repository`
- Cross-feature communication via Spring Application Events only
  - Never call `EmailService` directly from `AuthService` ‚Äî publish an event instead
- No Hexagonal/DDD out of the box

## Code conventions

- Java 21: use Records for DTOs, Pattern Matching where it improves clarity
- Constructor injection only ‚Äî never `@Autowired` on fields
- Never expose JPA entities directly in API responses ‚Äî always use DTOs
- SLF4J structured logging with key-value pairs ‚Äî no string concatenation
- Only implement what is explicitly requested ‚Äî no speculative extras
- Delete old code when replacing an implementation ‚Äî no dead code
- Formatting: Google Java Style via Spotless (`./gradlew spotlessApply`)

## REST API

- Base path: `/api/v1/`
- Error format: RFC 7807 `ProblemDetail` (`application/problem+json`)
- Validation: Jakarta annotations (`@Valid`, `@NotBlank`, etc.)

## Database

- Table names: `snake_case` plural ‚Äî `users`, `refresh_tokens`
- Every table has: `id` (UUID), `created_at`, `updated_at`
- Migrations: `src/main/resources/db/migration/V{n}__{description}.sql`
- Never use `ddl-auto: create` or `update` ‚Äî Flyway owns all schema changes

## Security

- Do not document security implementation details (algorithms, cipher suites, etc.) in any file ‚Äî helps attackers
- CORS configured via `CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS` env var

## Required actions when changing code

- Update `docs/en/` and `docs/ja/` when adding or changing a feature
- Update or create the corresponding `.http` file in `requests/` when adding or modifying an API endpoint

## Out of scope

Frontend, Kafka, GraphQL, gRPC, Kubernetes, WebSocket, multi-tenancy, soft delete, feature flags.

## Before starting

1. Read `AGENTS.md`
2. Read `AGENTS.dev.md` if it exists (gitignored ‚Äî contains private maintainer context)
3. Read `ARCHITECTURE.md` for system design overview
